<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-731-979  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 731 979.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lasers andamp; Optronics  Dec 1990 v9 n12 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Newport actively isolates the world.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Weiss, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Asystem to mount optical equipment so ground vibrations andairborne noise are sensed and nullified has been developed byNewport.andP;  The system uses an active response table called EVIS(Electronic Vibration Isolation System).andP;  The table is 2 feet x 3feet and weighs 280 pounds.andP;  It senses the onset of small motionsin the 1-100 Hz range, amplifies the signal, and generates acontinuously variable opposing motion to wipe out the vibrations.andO;The same isolation reduction found in a space vehicle can beachieved by EVIS.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     NoiseResearch and DevelopmentOpticsVibration.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Transmission of noise frequencies by Newport's EVIS activeresponse table. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>